<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-415-329  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 415 329.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Sept 10 1990 n607 p48(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Real-time system simulator. (Ready Systems introducesVRTXdesigner) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Weiss, Ray.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Ready Systems of Sunnyvale, CA introduces a top-down design toolfor batch-run simulation of real-time applications, VRTXdesigner.andO;The software package runs under the VRTX 32 real-time operatingsystem and features an icon-oriented graphical design methodologyfor defining and relating application modules.andP;  VRTXdesignerenables the circuit designer to link the design to the underlyingVRTX 32 kernel; simulate and monitor real-time operation; verifycritical timing aspects, task preemption, and processorutilization; and check for processing bottlenecks, timingviolations, conflicts and deadlocks.andP;  The application modules canuse the VRTX 32 kernel's various scheduling and processingmechanisms.andP;  Parameters for external world factors can be input todrive the simulation.andP;  VRTXdesigner will ship in Oct 1990 for$9,950 for a single-user Sun workstation version.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ready Systems (product introduction).andO;Product:   VRTXdesigner (Program development software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Real-Time SystemsProgram Development ToolsSpecificationsSimulationSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>